    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-11T11:29:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-11T11:29:00-05:00" n="427"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d427">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/1277</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Francis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Petrograd</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-11T19:00:00+02:31">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 11, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received February 14, 10.41 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2358. The Brest negotiations terminated. Following declaration signed by
                        <persName corresp="#p_TLDB1">Trotsky</persName> and Russian delegation, also
                    by Bolshevik Ukraine delegation, formally promulgated by Smolny: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>In the name of People’s Commissaries, which is government of Russian
                            Federated Republic, we hereby bring to knowledge of governments and
                            peoples at war with us, to our allies and to neutral countries, that,
                            refusing to sign an annexationist treaty, Russia vdeclares on her part
                            the state of war with Germany. Austria-Hungary, Turkey and Bulgaria has
                            ceased, that the Russian troops are simultaneously given orders to
                            demobilize completely on all fronts.</p>
                        <pb facs="0503" n="429" xml:id="pg_429"/>
                        <p>This not greatly surprising, except not expected so soon. It is
                            equivalent to separate peace which I think would have been formally
                            signed if Soviet had been recognized by Allies. Must await developments
                            to give information concerning commercial treaty, which think Germany
                            negotiating with Soviet. Have sent commercial attaché to the Department
                            [of] Industry to cultivate unofficial trade relations. Vigilance
                            required to check German commercial activities. <persName
                                corresp="#p_AGMV1">Alexeev</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_KGAM1"
                                >Kaledin</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_KGLG1"
                                >Kornilov</persName> will not disband forces.</p>
                        <p>Germany reported to have given Rumania notice that hostilities will be
                            resumed if peace unsigned four days.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_FDR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
